<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[130,646,164,1730]" box="[130,254,1227,1253]" pageId="16" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis box="[130,254,1227,1253]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="82">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[130,646,164,1730]" lastBlockId="16.[683,1199,163,1731]" pageId="16" pageNumber="82">
Individuals were captured in harp-traps set in the forest at Baai, Marang and Tintang formations. It was also captured in Gua Kelelawar at the Tintang formation. Its dis- tribution is limited to scattered localities in 
<collectingRegion box="[130,205,1431,1457]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="16" pageNumber="82">Sabah</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[218,319,1431,1457]" name="Malaysia" pageId="16" pageNumber="82">Sarawak</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[380,460,1431,1457]" name="Brunei" pageId="16" pageNumber="82">Brunei</collectingCountry>
and Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[130,241,1465,1491]" name="Malaysia" pageId="16" pageNumber="82">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
. Records from Sangkulirang are amongst only three for 
<collectingRegion box="[434,575,1499,1525]" country="Indonesia" name="Kalimantan Utara" pageId="16" pageNumber="82">Kalimantan</collectingRegion>
. It is known to roost in caves, rocky outcrops and hollow trees and to forage in little-disturbed forest (
<bibRefCitation author="PAYNE, J. B. &amp; C. M. FRANCIS &amp; K. PHILLIPS &amp; KARTI- KASARI" bookContentInfo="386 pp." box="[214,439,1601,1628]" journalOrPublisher="Jakarta" pageId="16" pageNumber="82" refId="ref18934" refString="PAYNE, J. B., C. M. FRANCIS, K. PHILLIPS, and KARTI- KASARI. 2000. Panduan lapangan mamalia di Ka- limantan, Sabah, Sarawak dan Brunei Darussalam [A field guide to the mammals of Kalimantan, Sa- bah, Sarawak and Brunei Darussalam]. Wildlife Conservation Society Indonesia Program, The Sa- bah Society and WWF Malaysia, Jakarta, 386 pp." title="Panduan lapangan mamalia di Ka- limantan, Sabah, Sarawak dan Brunei Darussalam [A field guide to the mammals of Kalimantan, Sa- bah, Sarawak and Brunei Darussalam]. Wildlife Conservation Society Indonesia Program, The Sa- bah Society and WWF Malaysia" type="book" year="2000">
Payne 
<emphasis box="[297,358,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
, 2000
</bibRefCitation>
). Our captures in the burnt vegetation around Baai suggest that it may also utilise secondary forests if roost resources are still available. 
